<P N="13">13 Some read it, <HI>by thy Sword.</HI> Others, By the <HI>Sword,</HI> &s;uppo&s;e the <HI>Ark</HI> to be meant, which was as th<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> <HI>Sword</HI> of God for the Defence of <HI>I&s;rael,</HI> and the O&s;ten<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> of their Enemies. The P&s;almi&s;t prays, they &s;ay, <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">o<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> the <HI>Deliverance</HI> of that, as for his own <HI>Soul.</HI></P>
