<DIV2 N="72" TYPE="Psalm">
<PB N="181" REF="001946_0218_0FFCB7D276E5D928">
<HEAD>PSALM LXXII. <HI>Of Solomon.</HI></HEAD>
<P N="1">1 GIve Thou unto the King, O God, &Verbar; Thy Judgments of all &s;orts; &Verbar; and unto the Son of the King &Verbar; <HI>give thou</HI> thy Righteou&s;ne&s;s. &Verbar;</P>
<P N="2">2 He to thy People &s;hall di&s;pen&s;e &Verbar; Judg|ments in Righteou&s;ne&s;s; &Verbar; and with right Judgment he &s;hall treat &Verbar; Thy poor afflicted ones. &Verbar;</P>
<P N="3">3 The mountains to thy People &s;hall &Verbar; bring forth a pro&s;p'rous peace; &Verbar; and &s;o the little hills &s;hall do, &Verbar; becau&s;e of righteou&s;ne&s;s. &Verbar;</P>
<P N="4">4 The poor afflicted ones among &Verbar; the Peo|ple He &s;hall judge: &Verbar; He'll the Sons of the needy &s;ave; &Verbar; and break th' injurious one. &Verbar;</P>
<P N="5">5 Even &s;o long as does the Sun &Verbar; their fear of thee &s;hall la&s;t: &Verbar; and while the Moon &s;hall have a face; &Verbar; from Age to Age 'twill be. &Verbar;</P>
<P N="6">6 He &s;hall come down like to the Rain &Verbar; upon the Gra&s;s that's mown: &Verbar; <HI>There &s;hall be a de&s;cent</HI> like to &Verbar; Show'rs watering of the Earth. &Verbar;</P>
<P N="7">7 Whoever is the righteous one &Verbar; &s;hall flouri&s;h in His days; &Verbar; and there &s;hall be great &s;tore of Peace, &Verbar; while there &s;hall be no Moon. &Verbar;</P>
<P N="8">8 And He &s;hall His Dominion &s;pread &Verbar; a|broad from Sea to Sea; &Verbar; yea, from the River <HI>it &s;hall &s;pread</HI> &Verbar; to the ends of the Earth. &Verbar;</P>
<P N="9"><PB N="182" REF="001946_0219_0FFCB387860BA350">
9 They who dwell in the wilderne&s;s be|fore Him &s;hall bow down: &Verbar; and they that are his enemies &s;hall lick the very du&s;t. &Verbar;</P>
<P N="10">10 The Kings of Tar&s;is and the I&s;les, &Verbar; &s;hall bring their pre&s;ents <HI>then;</HI> &Verbar; Then Sheba's Kings and Seba's too, &Verbar; &s;hall offer Gifts <HI>to Him.</HI> &Verbar;</P>
<P N="11">11 Yea, Kings of ev'ry Kingdom &s;hall &Verbar; before Him bow them&s;elves; &Verbar; all Nations &s;hall <HI>therewith</HI> become &Verbar; liege Servants unto Him. &Verbar;</P>
<P N="13">13 For he &s;hall &s;ave the needy one, &Verbar; upon his piteous cry, &Verbar; and <HI>&s;ave</HI> the poor afflicted one, &Verbar; yea, him whom none will help.</P>
<P N="13">13 He &s;hall a kind compa&s;&s;ion &s;hew &Verbar; to him that's de&s;titute; &Verbar; and to the needy; yea, He'll &s;ave &Verbar; the Souls of needy ones. &Verbar;</P>
<P N="14">14 From fraud, and from iniquity, &Verbar; He &s;hall redeem their Souls; &Verbar; their Blood &s;hall al&s;o be e&s;teem'd &Verbar; precious before His eyes. &Verbar;</P>
<P N="15">15 <HI>This Poor</HI> &s;hall live &s;o, and <HI>the King</HI> &Verbar; &s;hall give him Sheba's Gold; &Verbar; And He'll &s;till intercede for him; &Verbar; He'll ble&s;s him every day. &Verbar;</P>
<P N="16">16 Of Corn an handful there &s;hall be &Verbar; <HI>then &s;een</HI> upon the Earth; &Verbar; Upon the very top of the &Verbar; high mountains, <HI>&s;own and &s;een.</HI> &Verbar; The fruit thereof &s;hall make its wave &Verbar; ev'n like tol, ebanon; &Verbar; The Citizens &s;hall flouri&s;h then &Verbar; like the Gra&s;s of the Earth. &Verbar;</P>
<P N="18">18 His Name, that &s;hall endure unto &Verbar;
<PB N="183" REF="001946_0220_0FFCB394CB279B28">all perpetuity: &Verbar; in the face of the Sur He &s;hall, have the Name of, The Son. &Verbar; And it &s;hall u&s;ual be for Men, to ble&s;s them&s;elves in Him: &Verbar; All Nations <HI>of the World,</HI> they &s;hall &Verbar; call Him, The ble&s;&s;ed One. &Verbar;</P>
<P N="18">18 O ble&s;&s;ed be <HI>the Glorious</HI> God, who is the ETERNAL One; <HI>&Verbar; Ble&s;s'd be</HI> the God of I&s;rael who <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word"> alone does wondrous things. &Verbar;</P>
<P N="19">19 Yea, ever ble&s;s'd His Glorious Name: &Verbar; And now let all the Earth &Verbar; be with His <HI>wondrous</HI> Glory fill'd: &Verbar; Amen, <HI>O &s;ay,</HI> Amen. &Verbar;</P>
<P N="20">20 <HI>With &s;uch in&s;pir'd de&s;ires as the&s;e,</HI> the Supplications of David, who was Je&s;&s;e's Son, have come unto their end.</P>
<DIV3 TYPE="explanation">
<HEAD>ILLUSTRATIONS on the LXXII. PSALM.</HEAD>
<P>TIs a Traver for the Coming and Kin<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters">om of the <HI>Me&s;&s;iah.</HI> The Jews unanimou&s;ly apply it unto Him 1 A praefarory Wi&s;h for the Pro&s;perity of the P&s;al|mi&s;t him&s;elf, and of His Son <HI>Solomon,</HI> to whom the P&s;alm is dedicated. &mdash; The Subject of the follow|ing P&s;alm is another, a Greater than he.</P>
<P N="16">16 An <HI>handful of Corn</HI> &s;own even on the Top <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word"> Barren Mountains, will &s;pring up with <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">ar<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">, win<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters"> will be &s;o thick and full, that when they are &s;ua<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">en with the Wind, they &s;hall make a Noi&s;e like the C<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">|dars of <HI>Lebanon.</HI> The <HI>City</HI> &s;hall be as truitful as the <HI>Country,</HI> and as well &s;tored with Good things, as th<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> Earth is with Gra&s;s in the Spring. This is the <HI>Patrician</HI> Paraphra&s;e.</P>
<P N="17">17 The Hebrews call the Me&s;&s;iah by the Name of <HI>Jinn<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">n,</HI> which &s;ignifies <HI>A Son</HI> Here <HI>Before the Sun, Jinn<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">n</HI> is <HI>Hi<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> Name.</HI> The <HI>Midra&s;h Till<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters"></HI> rea<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters"> it
<PB N="184" REF="001946_0221_0FFCB38DEB31D898"><HI>Ante Solem filiabit Nomen ejus.</HI> And adds this Glo&s;s upon it; &mdash; <HI>Quia ip&s;e filiaturus est Dormient&eacute;s in Pulvere.</HI></P>
<P>This is Wondrous from the Pen of a Jew!</P>
<P>I have &s;omewhere &s;een this Glo&s;s and thought upon it. <HI>His Name &s;hall be as a Son, to continue his Fa|ther's Name forever.</HI> Thus the Mini&s;ters of the Word, ought to <HI>rai&s;e up the Name of</HI> CHRIST <HI>upon His In|heritance,</HI> His Church. They ought not to <HI>rai&s;e up</HI> their <HI>own Names.</HI></P>
<P>This Pa&s;&s;age, <HI>Nomen ejus filiabatur,</HI> is fulfilled un|to our Saviour, in that His <HI>Name</HI> is continued by the Succe&s;&s;ion of <HI>Many Sons,</HI> before the <HI>Sun.</HI> Compare Heb. II. 13.</P>
</DIV3>
