<DIV2 N="104" TYPE="Psalm">
<HEAD>PSALM CIV.</HEAD>
<P N="1">1 MY Soul, Ble&s;s thou th' ETERNAL God; &Verbar; ETERNAL God, my God, &Verbar; Thou'rt very great, Thou'rt cloathed with &Verbar; Honour and Maje&s;ty. &Verbar;</P>
<P N="2">2 As with a Garment on Him He &Verbar; covers Him&s;elf with Light; &Verbar; He doth extend the Heavens like &Verbar; a curtain round about. &Verbar;</P>
<P N="3">3 He on the Waters lays the beams &Verbar; of's chambers; He doth make &Verbar; the Clouds His chariot; He doth walk &Verbar; on the wings of the wind. &Verbar;</P>
<P N="4">4 He doth make Spirits for to be &Verbar; Angels <HI>&s;ent forth by Him,</HI> &Verbar; and He a flaming fire does make &Verbar; to be His Mini&s;ters. &Verbar;</P>
<P N="5">5 Upon the Ba&s;es for it He &Verbar; has founded well the Earth; &Verbar; &s;o that it &s;hall not be remov'd; &Verbar; no, not from Age to Age. &Verbar;</P>
<P N="6">6 As with a Garment thou did&s;t hide &Verbar; it with the va&s;t aby&s;s; &Verbar; <HI>At fir&s;t</HI> above the mountains did &Verbar; the waters take their place. &Verbar;</P>
<P N="7"><PB N="274" REF="001946_0311_0FFCB51B9909D210">
