<P N="32">32 And at the Waters of <HI>their</HI> &s;trife &Verbar; they rais'd a boiling wrath; &Verbar; &s;o that with Mo&s;es there it went &Verbar; but ill on their account. &Verbar;</P>
<P N="33">33 Becau&s;e that they his &s;pirit threw&Verbar;into great bitterne&s;s, &Verbar; and then he brought forth with his lips&Verbar; <HI>what &s;hould not have been there.</HI> &Verbar;</P>
<P N="34">34 Tho&s;e <HI>cur&s;ed</HI> Peoples they did not &Verbar; wholly exterminate, &Verbar; concerning whom th' ETERNAL God &Verbar; had &s;o commanded them. &Verbar;</P>
<P N="35">35 But they did mix them&s;elves among &Verbar; the heathen Nations there, &Verbar; and they did learn <HI>to do</HI> their works; &Verbar; <HI>ev'n their Idolatries</HI> &Verbar;</P>
<P N="36">36 And they did &s;erve their Idols which &Verbar; became a &s;nare to them. &Verbar;</P>
<P N="37">37 Yea, they to Devils &s;acrific'd &Verbar; their Daughters with their Sons. &Verbar;</P>
<P N="38">38 So they pour'd out the Blood of &s;uch &Verbar; as were poor Innocents; &Verbar; It was the Blood of their own Sons &Verbar; and of their Daughters too. &Verbar; The&s;e unto Canaan's Idols they &Verbar; did make their &s;acrifice; &Verbar; and with &s;uch bloody doings was &Verbar; the very Land defil'd. &Verbar;</P>
<P N="39">39 Thus with their <HI>dete&s;table</HI> works &Verbar; they did pollute them&s;elves; &Verbar; and &s;o they did a<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters"> whoring with &Verbar; their own Inventions go. &Verbar;</P>
<P N="40">40 Now the wrath of the ETERNAL God &Verbar; again&s;t His People ro&s;e; &Verbar; and He did now abominate &Verbar; His own Inheritance. &Verbar;</P>
<P N="41"><PB N="289" REF="001946_0326_0FFCB680A7670940">
41 And He deliver'd them into &Verbar; the hand of Gentiles then; &Verbar; and they that hated them did bear &Verbar; dominion over them. &Verbar;</P>
<P N="42">42 And they that were their Enemies &Verbar; &s;orely oppre&s;&s;ed them, &Verbar; yea, and they were under their hand &Verbar; into &s;ubjection brought. &Verbar;</P>
<P N="43">43 He many times delivered them; &Verbar; But with their coun&s;el they &Verbar; provoked &s;till, and were brought low &Verbar; for their iniquity. &Verbar;</P>
<P N="44">44 Neverthele&s;s He did behold, &Verbar; when upon them there was &Verbar; Affliction, when <HI>therein</HI> He heard &Verbar; them making of their cry. &Verbar;</P>
<P N="45">45 And He for them His Covenant &Verbar; did to remembrance call; &Verbar; after His mercies multitude &Verbar; it then repented Him. &Verbar;</P>
<P N="46">46 He al&s;o to compa&s;&s;ions did &Verbar; kindly de|liver them &Verbar; before the face of all of tho&s;e &Verbar; that captivated them. &Verbar;</P>
<P N="47">47 O Thou ETERNAL God, our God, &Verbar; To us O do thou grant &Verbar; Salvation, and, Oh! from among &Verbar; the Nations gather us: &Verbar; That &s;o we may confe&s;s to the &Verbar; Name of thy Holy One, &Verbar; and that we may triumphantly &Verbar; &s;ing forth thy Glorious Prai&s;e. &Verbar;</P>
<P N="48">48 Ble&s;s'd be th' ETERNAL God, the God &Verbar; of I&s;rael evermore; &Verbar; And let all People &s;ay, Amen. &Verbar; <HI>Sing</HI> Hallelujah <HI>now!</HI> &Verbar;</P>
<DIV3 TYPE="explanation">
<HEAD>ILLUSTRATIONS on the CVI. PSALM.</HEAD>
<P>THE <HI>Prophotic Spirit</HI> prepares an humble Confe&s;&s;ion to be made by the Jews, concerning the Sins of
<PB N="290" REF="001946_0327_0FFCB687F5D55F40">their Fathers, and an humble Petition for Deliverance from their Di&s;per&s;ion.</P>
<P>Some imagine the P&s;alm to be compos'd in the Ti<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="3 letters"> of the <HI>Babylonlan</HI> Captivity; becau&s;e of <HI>Gather <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word"> from among the Heathen.</HI> Dr. <HI>Patrick</HI> rather &s;uppo&s;t this Petition to refer unto tho&s;e, who in the Days <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word"> <HI>Saul,</HI> or before, were taken Pri&s;oners by the <HI>Phili&s;ti<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters"></HI> and other Nations.</P>
<P N="15">15 <HI>Mun&s;ter</HI> &s;ays, 'Tis a Phra&s;e for <HI>Death.</HI></P>
<P N="17">17 Why no mention made of <HI>Korah?</HI> The P&s;alm was to be Sung by the Sons of <HI>Korah.</HI> And R. <HI>Solo<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">|mon</HI> ob&s;erves, <HI>Honor at Filios Cora, et not memi<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="3 letters"> Patris eorum.</HI></P>
<P N="30">30 To <HI>Stand</HI> in <HI>Prayer,</HI> was a Po&s;ture &s;o u&s;ual amo<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters"> the Jews, that it became a Phra&s;e for <HI>Prayer.</HI> The Jews here con&s;ider <HI>Phinehas</HI> as <HI>Praying</HI> before his Action.</P>
</DIV3>
