<P>The Jewi&s;h conce&s;&s;ions for our Chri&s;tian Application of the <HI>P&s;<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">lm,</HI> are Numerous and Marvellous. The <HI>Midra&s;h Tillin</HI> particularly, quotes the, <HI>Sit thou at my Right hand,</HI> as belonging to the <HI>Me&s;&s;iah.</HI> And R. <HI>Obadiah</HI> &s;ays, <HI>The P&s;ami&s;t compo&s;ed this P&s;alm of the Me&s;&s;iah.</HI> And from the fir&s;t Ver&s;e, he places the <HI>Me&s;&s;iah,</HI> above the <HI>Angels</HI> of God.</P>
<P N="1">1 <HI>Sitting,</HI> when &s;poken of a King intends <HI>Reigning.</HI> Here is an <HI>A&s;&s;ociation</HI> in Government. The Sceptre comes between them. <HI>Vitring<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"></HI> writes finely on it.</P>
