<P N="16">16 <HI>Calvin</HI> ob&s;erves, the meaning of this to be That the Infinite GOD, is forever &s;atisfied in and from Him&s;elf; He needs no <HI>Earthly</HI> thing to augment <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters">is Happine&s;s. The <HI>Earth</HI> with all the Enjoyments of it, He allows to the Poor Children of Men. All He ex|pects from the <HI>Earth</HI> is a Thankful Acknowledgment from the relieved and obliged Children of Men. <HI>Ho<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> Propheta Con&s;ilium e&s;t, quod miror tum &s;ecture a ple|ri&s;yuc inter pretibus negligi.</HI></P>
<P N="17">17 q. d. <Q>Therefore He will not &s;uffer us to be rooted out, as our Enemies de&s;ign; for then the Earth would have none in it, to &s;ing His Prai&s;es; which the Dead who dwell in the &s;ilent Grave cannot celebrate.</Q> This is the <HI>Patrician</HI> Faraphra&s;e.</P>
