<P N="1">1 I'll Sing to the ETERNAL God &Verbar; who triumphs glo|riou&s;ly: &Verbar; The Hor&s;e with him that rides him, He &Verbar; has thrown into the Sea. &Verbar;</P>
<P N="2">2 Now the ETERNAL God becomes &Verbar; my Strength, and <HI>&s;o my</HI> Song; &Verbar; and He it is who hath been for &Verbar; Sal|vation unto me. &Verbar; He is my God, and I'll prepare &Verbar; for Him a Dwelling-place; &Verbar; He of my Father is the God, &Verbar; and I'll &s;et Him on high. &Verbar;</P>
<P N="3">3 He who is the ETERNAL God &Verbar; does yet become a Man &Verbar; <HI>a Man</HI> of War; 'tis He of whom &Verbar; JEHOVAH is the Name. &Verbar;</P>
<P N="6">6 Thy Right hand O ETERNAL God, &Verbar; is glorify'd with pow'r; &Verbar; Thy Right hand O ETERNAL God &Verbar; has broke the Enemy. &Verbar;</P>
<P N="7">7 Tho&s;e who again&s;t thee ri&s;e, Thou wilt &Verbar; in thy great Excellence &Verbar; pull down; Thou<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">'t &s;end thy wrath; it &s;hall &Verbar; like &s;tubble them con&s;ume. &Verbar;</P>
<P N="11">11 Among the God's, who's like to Thee, &Verbar; O Thou ETERNAL God! &Verbar; Who's like to Thee; In holine&s;s &Verbar; &s;o very Glorious <HI>who!</HI> &Verbar; Thou in thy Glorious Prai&s;es art &Verbar; how very terrible! &Verbar; Thou art the doer of the thing &Verbar; that is mo&s;t wonderful. &Verbar;</P>
<P N="13">13 The People which thou ha&s;t redeem'd &Verbar; in thy benignity &Verbar; thou ha&s;t led forth; &Verbar; Thou in thy &s;trength &Verbar; do&s;t a good conduct give, &Verbar; unto the Habitation of &Verbar; thy <HI>Glorious</HI> Holine&s;s. &Verbar;</P>
<P N="18">18 He, who is the ETERNAL God &Verbar; &s;hall reign for<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> evermore, &Verbar;</P>
