<DIV2 N="2" TYPE="part">
<PB N="412" REF="001946_0449_0FFE5A26D5B3A230">
<HEAD>II. The Mo&s;aic Prophecy.</HEAD>
<HEAD TYPE="sub"><HI>Deut.</HI> XXXII.</HEAD>
<P N="3">3 SInce I will own aloud the Name &Verbar; of the ETERNAL God; &Verbar; A mighty Greatne&s;s, O do ye &Verbar; A&s;cribe unto our God. &Verbar;</P>
<P N="4">4 The Rock; His Work is perfect; For &Verbar; Judgment's in all His ways; &Verbar; A God of truth; He does no wrong: &Verbar; mo&s;t ju&s;t and right is He. &Verbar;</P>
<P N="29">29 Oh! That they were once truly wi&s;e, &Verbar; That this they under hood! &Verbar; That they would think and know what &s;hall &Verbar; come in their latter end. &Verbar;</P>
<P N="36">36 For the ETERNAL God will for &Verbar; His People be a Judge; &Verbar; And for His Servants He will do &Verbar; as one who does repent! &Verbar; <HI>It &s;hall be done,</HI> when that He does &Verbar; behold their pow'r is gone, &Verbar; And there is none &s;hut up in <HI>Tow'res,</HI> &Verbar; no, not the lea&s;t re&s;erve. &Verbar;</P>
<P N="43">43 Sing O ye Nations, of what He &Verbar; will for His People do; &Verbar; Becau&s;e of His own Servants He &Verbar; will now revenge the blood: &Verbar; And Vengeance He will render to &Verbar; tho&s;e who have troubled them. &Verbar; So He'l &s;hew mercy to His Land, &Verbar; unto His People there. &Verbar;</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="3" TYPE="part">
<HEAD>III. The Song of the MESSIAH. [Or when the Name of the MESSIAH is fir&s;t mentioned.]</HEAD>
<HEAD TYPE="sub">I <HI>Sam.</HI> II.</HEAD>
<P N="1">1 IN the ETERNAL God my heart &Verbar; hath an exulting joy: &Verbar; In the ETERNAL God my Horn &Verbar; is li&s;ted up on high. &Verbar; Over my Adver&s;aries now &Verbar; I have an opened mouth; &Verbar; It is becau&s;e I do rejoyce &Verbar; in thy Salvation, <HI>Lord.</HI> &Verbar;</P>
<P N="2">2 There is not any Holy like &Verbar; to the ETERNAL God. &Verbar; And there is not a Rock to be &Verbar; compar'd unto our God. &Verbar;</P>
<P N="6">6 'Tis the ETERNAL God who kills; &Verbar; and He who makes to live. &Verbar; 'Tis He brings down unto the Pit &Verbar; and He who bringeth up. &Verbar;</P>
<P N="7">7 Th' ETERNAL God, He maketh Poor &Verbar; He al&s;o maketh Rich; &Verbar; 'Tis He who maketh down to fall; &Verbar; and He who lifteth up. &Verbar;</P>
<P N="9"><PB N="413" REF="001946_0450_0FFE5A2B5DBD24D8">
9 He of His gracious Ones will keep &Verbar; the feet; but wicked ones &Verbar; in darkne&s;s &s;hall be &s;ilent; for &Verbar; by &s;trength no Man prevails. &Verbar;</P>
<P N="10">10 Th' ETERNAL God, They who contend &Verbar; with Him &s;hall be de&s;troy'd; &Verbar; He in the Heaven's upon them &Verbar; &s;hall thunder down from thence. &Verbar; Th' ETERNAL God &s;hall be the Judge &Verbar; to the Fnds of the Earth; &Verbar; His King He'l &s;trengthen, and on high &Verbar; lift His MESSIAH's Horn. &Verbar;</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="4" TYPE="part">
<HEAD>IV. Divine Attraction Asked for.</HEAD>
<HEAD TYPE="sub">Cant. <HI>I.</HI></HEAD>
<P N="4">4 O Draw thou me; we &s;hall thereon &Verbar; be running after thee; &Verbar; Into His Chambers now the King &Verbar; hath introduced me. &Verbar; In thee we'll be exceeding glad, &Verbar; and have triumphant Joy; &Verbar; Thy Love we will mind more than Wine; &Verbar; Upright ones love thee &s;till. &Verbar;</P>
<P N="7">7 O Thou beloved of my Soul, &Verbar; Declare thou unto me, &Verbar; <HI>Declare</HI> where thou do&s;t feed <HI>thy Flock,</HI> &Verbar; and make them re&s;t at noon. &Verbar; For why &s;hould I be like unto &Verbar; One who does turn a&s;ide, &Verbar; * a <HI>vailed</HI> one, among the Flocks &Verbar; of thy Companions! &Verbar;</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="5" TYPE="part">
<HEAD>V. The Tree of Life.</HEAD>
<HEAD TYPE="sub">Cant. <HI>II.</HI></HEAD>
<P N="3">3 RE&s;embling of the Orange-tree &Verbar; among the other Trees &Verbar; of the Wood, my Beloved is &Verbar; among the other Sons. &Verbar; Under His ble&s;&s;ed Shadow, I &Verbar; &s;at down with great Delight, &Verbar; and to my palate was His Fruit &Verbar; mo&s;t wonderfully &s;weet. &Verbar;</P>
<P N="4">4 He introduced me into &Verbar; His Hou&s;e of Banquetting, &Verbar; And of His banner over me, &Verbar; the Motto, it was, LOVE. &Verbar;</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="6" TYPE="part">
<HEAD>VI. Flaming Love.</HEAD>
<HEAD TYPE="sub">Cant. <HI>VIII.</HI></HEAD>
<P N="6">6 O Set me as a Seal upon &Verbar; thine Heart; O <HI>&s;et me</HI> as &Verbar; a Seal upon thine Arm: For Love &Verbar; it is as &s;trong as Death. &Verbar; Oh! Jealou&s;y, it is &s;evere &Verbar; as is the very Crave; &Verbar; Its Arrows are Arrows of Fire, &Verbar; Flames of the Fire of God. &Verbar;</P>
<P N="7"><PB N="414" REF="001946_0451_0FFE5A2EC14D86D0">
7 Love, many Waters cannot quench, &Verbar; nor drown it can the Floods; &Verbar; &s;hould one give all He's worth for Love, &Verbar; it would be but de&s;pis'd. &Verbar;</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="7" TYPE="part">
<HEAD>VII. Repeated Songs of Salvation.</HEAD>
<HEAD TYPE="sub">I&s;aiah <HI>XII.</HI></HEAD>
<DIV3 TYPE="section">
<HEAD>The Former.</HEAD>
<P N="1">1 I'L Prai&s;e Thee, O ETERNAL God; &Verbar; Tho' thou waft wroth with me, &Verbar; Thy wrath is now all turn'd away, &Verbar; and thou wilt comfort me. &Verbar;</P>
<P N="2">2 LO, God's my SAVIOUR, I will tru&s;t &Verbar; and will not be afraid: &Verbar; For He who&s;e Glorious Name is JAH &Verbar; ev'n the ETERNAL God; &Verbar; Tis Him I have <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">o &s;trengthen me, &Verbar; and He &s;hall be my Song: &Verbar; He al&s;o 'tis that unto me &Verbar; a Saviour is become. &Verbar;</P>
<P N="3">3 And now with a mo&s;t &s;olid Joy, &Verbar; Waters you &s;hall draw forth &Verbar; from the &s;till flowing Fountains, which &Verbar; the Saviour has prepar'd. &Verbar;</P>
</DIV3>
<DIV3 TYPE="section">
<HEAD>The Latter.</HEAD>
<P N="4">4 O Prai&s;e ye the ETERNAL God, &Verbar; Call ye upon His Name; &Verbar; Among the People O declare &Verbar; the things perform'd by Him. &Verbar; Keep in remembrance, that His Name &Verbar; is now on high extoll'd. &Verbar;</P>
<P N="5">5 O utter now your Songs to Him &Verbar; who's the E|TERNAL God. &Verbar; For He has done what does proclain &Verbar; His high magnificence: &Verbar; This is a thing that is made known &Verbar; abroad in all the Earth. &Verbar;</P>
<P N="6">6 O Thou, who do&s;t in Zion dwell, &Verbar; Cry out and &s;hout aloud &Verbar; For Great is I&s;rael's Holy One &Verbar; who's in the mid&s;t of thee. &Verbar;</P>
</DIV3>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="8" TYPE="part">
<HEAD>VIII. The Song of the Strong City.</HEAD>
<HEAD TYPE="sub">I&s;ai. <HI>XXVI.</HI></HEAD>
<P N="1">1 THere is for us a City now &Verbar; of a &s;ufficient &s;trength; &Verbar; The SAVIOUR will afford to it &Verbar; Walls and a Bulwark too. &Verbar;</P>
<P N="2">Set open ye the Gates of it; &Verbar; and let then enter in &Verbar; the Righteous N<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">tion, which <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">oes keep &Verbar; the Truth; i<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> &mdash;</P>
<P N="3"><PB N="415" REF="001946_0452_0FFE5A305153C698">
3 E&s;tabli&s;hed is the Decree &Verbar; that thou wilt keep it &s;till &Verbar; in Peace, <HI>yea, in a glorious</HI> Peace, &Verbar; becau&s;e it hopes in thee. &Verbar;</P>
<P N="4">4 In the ETERNAL God, O put &Verbar; your tru&s;t for evermore; &Verbar; Becau&s;e a Rock of Ages is &Verbar; in JAH the ETERNAL God. &Verbar;</P>
<P N="9">9 Oh! with my very Soul I have &Verbar; de&s;ir'd thee in the Night; &Verbar; yea, with my Spirit in me I &Verbar; will early &s;eek for thee. &Verbar; For when thy Judgments are abroad &Verbar; di&s;|pen&s;ed in the Earth, &Verbar; They who are dwellers in the World &Verbar; &s;hall then learn Righteou&s;ne&s;s. &Verbar;</P>
<P N="12">12 O Thou ETERNAL God, Thou wilt &Verbar; accompli&s;h Peace for us, &Verbar; Becau&s;e that in and for us thou &Verbar; all of our works ha&s;t wrought. &Verbar;</P>
<P N="13">13 ETERNAL God, our God, Without &Verbar; Thee, Lords have ruled us; &Verbar; We with regard to thee alone &Verbar; will celebrate thy Name. &Verbar;</P>
<P N="20">20 Thy Dead &s;hall live again, they &s;hall &Verbar; as my Dead Body ri&s;e: &Verbar; Awake, and with, a triumph &s;ing, &Verbar; ye who dwell in the du&s;t. &Verbar; For thy dew &s;hall be like the dew &Verbar; which doth revive the Plants; &Verbar; and &s;o the Earth, it &s;hall &s;end &s;orth &Verbar; &s;uch as ly dead in it. &Verbar;</P>
<P N="21">21 <HI>In the mean time,</HI> Go then thy way &Verbar; thou, O my People, <HI>go</HI> &Verbar; Enter into thy Chambers, and &Verbar; about thee &s;hut thy door. &Verbar; There hide thy &s;elf; it will but as &Verbar; a little moment be, &Verbar; until the indigration &s;hall &Verbar; be wholly pa&s;t and gone. &Verbar;</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="9" TYPE="part">
<HEAD>IX. The Lord's Prayer.</HEAD>
<P>OUr Father who art in the Heav'ns; &dagger; <HI>[Olet]</HI> thy Name be &s;anctify'd; &dagger; Thy Kingdom, Oh! may it arrive; &dagger; Thy Will, may that be <HI>[fully]</HI> done. &dagger; <HI>Done</HI> here upon the Farth below, &dagger; as <HI>it is done</HI> in Heav'n <HI>[Above:]</HI> &dagger; This Day be&s;tow thou upon us &dagger; what is <HI>[to be]</HI> our Daily Bread. &dagger; And us our Debts for|give, as we &dagger; our Debtors <HI>[freely]</HI> do forgive; &dagger; And to Temptation lead us not, &dagger; but us from <HI>[the wor&s;t]</HI> evil &s;ave. &dagger;
<PB N="416" REF="001946_0453_0FFE5A3345221258">Becau&s;e the Kingdom, it is thine, &dagger; The Power too, <HI>'tis thine <HI>[alone;]</HI></HI> &dagger; And <HI>thine</HI> the Glory <HI>&s;till will be</HI> &dagger; Forevermore. Amen. <HI>[Amen.]</HI> &dagger;</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="10" TYPE="part">
<HEAD>X. Tydings from Heaven.</HEAD>
<HEAD TYPE="sub"><HI>Luk,</HI> II, 10, 11, 14.</HEAD>
<P>THe Angel &s;aid to them, Fear not, &dagger; For, Lo, I bring [<HI>from Head'n]</HI> to you &dagger; Good tydings of exceeding Joy; &dagger; <HI>[and &s;uch]</HI> 'twill to all People be. &dagger; For now a SAVIOUR unto you &dagger; this Day <HI>a <HI>[Bighty] <HI>SAVIOUR's</HI></HI></HI> Born; &dagger; 'Tis in your DAVID's City &s;o; &dagger; He is the CHRIST, the <HI>[Glorious]</HI> Lord.]</P>
<P>And with the Angel &s;uddenly &dagger; there was a <HI>[won|drous]</HI> Multitude &dagger; of the Cele&s;tial Army, which &dagger; then Prai&s;ed God, and <HI>[thus they]</HI> &s;aid; &dagger; O! In the Highe&s;t let there be &dagger; Now Glory <HI>[given]</HI> unto God; &dagger; And now on Earth let there be Peace; &dagger; In Men Benig|nity <HI>[be &s;een.]</HI> &dagger;</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="11" TYPE="part">
<HEAD>XI. The Lord our Healer.</HEAD>
<DIV3 TYPE="section">
<HEAD><HI>Mal.</HI> IV. 2.</HEAD>
<P>TO you that fear my Name there &s;hall &dagger; the <HI>[Slendid]</HI> Sun of Righteou&s;ne&s;s &dagger; ari&s;e with bealing vertue in &dagger; the rays <HI>[that be]</HI> &s;hot forth from Him &dagger;</P>
</DIV3>
<DIV3 TYPE="section">
<HEAD><HI>Matth,</HI> XI. 4, 5.</HEAD>
<P>THo&s;e things which ye do hear and &s;ee: &dagger; The Blind receive their <HI>[wi&s;h'd for]</HI> &s;ight; &dagger; And they that were the Lame do walk; &dagger; The Lepers are made clean <HI>[and whole.]</HI> &dagger; And they that were the Deaf do hear; &dagger; The Dead are <HI>[al&s;o]</HI> rai&s;ed up; &dagger; And they that are poor Creatures, &s;uch &dagger; <HI>[Ev'n &s;uch]</HI> as the&s;e are Go&s;pelliz'd. &dagger;</P>
</DIV3>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="12" TYPE="part">
<HEAD>XII. The Beatitudes.</HEAD>
<HEAD TYPE="sub"><HI>Matth.</HI> V. 3.&mdash;13.</HEAD>
<P N="1">I. BLe&s;&s;ed the Poor in Spirit are, &dagger; for theirs the Kingdom of the Heavens. &dagger;</P>
<P N="2">II. Ble&s;&s;ed are very Mournful ones, &dagger; for that they &s;hall be Comforted. &dagger;</P>
<P N="3"><PB N="417" REF="001946_0454_0FFE5B07ADB26CE0">
III. Ble&s;&s;ed the Meekly Patient are, &dagger; for they inhe|rit &s;hall the Earth. &dagger;</P>
<P N="4">IV. Ble&s;&s;ed, who Hunger and who Thir&s;t &dagger; for Ju&s;tice; for they &s;hall be fill'd. &dagger;</P>
<P N="5">V. Ble&s;&s;ed &s;hall be the Merciful, &dagger; for Mercy's what they &s;hall obtain. &dagger;</P>
<P N="6">VI. Ble&s;&s;ed &s;hall be the Pure in Heart, &dagger; for they &s;hall have the &s;ight of God. &dagger;</P>
<P N="7">VII. Ble&s;&s;ed the Peace-Makers: for they &dagger; &s;hall be pronounc'd the Sons of God. &dagger;</P>
<P N="8">VIII. Ble&s;s'd the pur&s;u'd for Righteon&s;ne&s;s; &dagger; for theirs, the Kingdom of the Heavens. &dagger;</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="13" TYPE="part">
<HEAD>XIII. The Song of <HI>Simeon.</HI></HEAD>
<HEAD TYPE="sub"><HI>Luk.</HI> II. 24,&mdash;32.</HEAD>
<P>O Lord, Thou in a ble&s;&s;ed Peace &Verbar; thy Servant do&s;t di&s;mi&s;s, &Verbar; Now <HI>after all that I have &s;een</HI> &Verbar; ac|cording to thy Word. &Verbar; For of thy Great Salvation now &Verbar; my Eyes have had the &s;ight: &Verbar; which thou before the Face of all &Verbar; People prepared ha&s;t: &Verbar; A Light by which the Gentales are &Verbar; to be enlighten'd <HI>all:</HI> &Verbar; And the bright Glory &s;hining to &Verbar; thy People I&s;rael. &Verbar;</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="14" TYPE="part">
<HEAD>XIV. A Golden Chain.</HEAD>
<HEAD TYPE="sub">2 <HI>Pet.</HI> I. 5, 6, 7.</HEAD>
<P>GIving all Diligence, O add, &Verbar; Courage unto your Faith; &Verbar; and unto Courage Knowledge <HI>add;</HI> &Verbar; to Knowledge, Temperance: &Verbar; And unto Temperance <HI>let there</HI> &Verbar; <HI>be added</HI> Godline&s;s. &Verbar; And unto Godline&s;s <HI>do you</HI> &Verbar; Brotherly kindne&s;s <HI>add:</HI> &Verbar; But to Brotherly kindne&s;s <HI>let</HI> &Verbar; <HI>be added</HI> Charity. &Verbar;</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="15" TYPE="part">
<HEAD>XV. Patience.</HEAD>
<HEAD TYPE="sub"><HI>Jam.</HI> I. 4, 5.</HEAD>
<P>LEt Patience have the perfect work &Verbar; <HI>which does be|long to it;</HI> &Verbar; &s;o you'l be perfect and entire &Verbar; de|<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">c<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">ent in no point. &Verbar; But if that any of you are &Verbar; &s;en&s;i|ble that he wants &Verbar; the Wi&s;dom, <HI>which is now propos'd,</HI> &Verbar;
<PB N="418" REF="001946_0455_0FFE51CBDD6B72C8">let him ask it of God; &Verbar; Who hath a liberal hand unto &Verbar; all Men does freely give, &Verbar; and don't upbraid <HI>their fooli&s;ima&s;s:</HI> &Verbar; &s;o 'twill be given him. &Verbar;</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="16" TYPE="part">
<HEAD>XVI. A Song in the Night.</HEAD>
<HEAD TYPE="sub"><HI>Heb.</HI> XII.</HEAD>
<P N="5">5 MY <HI>[Cha&s;tned]</HI> Son, De&s;pi&s;e thou not &dagger; the Cha&s;t|ning of the Lord; &dagger; nor do thou faint when that thou do&s;t &dagger; receive Rebukes from Him. &dagger;</P>
<P N="6">6 For whom the Lord doth <HI>[truly]</HI> love &dagger; He cha&s;t|neth &s;uch a one: &dagger; and &s;courgeth ev'ry one whom He &dagger; receiveth as a Son. &dagger;</P>
<P N="7">7 If Cha&s;tning ye <HI>[do well]</HI> endure &dagger; God deals with you as Sons; &dagger; for what Son ever is there, whom &dagger; the Father Cha&s;tens not? &dagger;</P>
<P N="10">10 He Cha&s;tens us <HI>['tis true]</HI> but it &dagger; is for our bene|fit; &dagger; 'tis that Partakers &s;o we might &dagger; be of His Holine&s;s, &dagger;</P>
<P N="11">11 Now for the pre&s;ent, there <HI>[he &s;ure]</HI> &dagger; no Cha&s;t|ning is that &s;eems &dagger; to be a cau&s;e of any joy, &dagger; no, but a cau&s;e of grief. &dagger; Yet a&s;terwards it. <HI>[&s;urely]</HI> yields &dagger; the fruit of Righteou&s;ne&s;s &dagger; to them that are well-tri'd thereby; &dagger; which will be full of Peace. &dagger;</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="17" TYPE="part">
<HEAD>XVII. The Faithful Saying.</HEAD>
<DIV3 TYPE="section">
<HEAD>1 <HI>Tim.</HI> I. 15.</HEAD>
<P>THis is a Saying, which de&s;erves &dagger; <HI>[Over]</HI> to be re|ly'd upon, &dagger; and it is worthy of a full &dagger; Reception ev'ry where <HI>[of all.]</HI> &dagger; <HI>This,</HI> That CHRIST <HI>who is</HI> JESUS, has &dagger; Now come into the <HI>[Ruin'd]</HI> World &dagger; for this, that unto Sinners, He &dagger; might be a <HI>[Mighty]</HI> SAVIOUR. &dagger;</P>
</DIV3>
<DIV3 TYPE="section">
<HEAD>The Matchle&s;s Gift.</HEAD>
<HEAD TYPE="sub"><HI>John</HI> III. 16.</HEAD>
<P>SUch, <HI>Even &s;uch,</HI> a Love has God &dagger; had for a <HI>[Lo&s;t and] <HI>Dying</HI></HI> World, &dagger; that He His Only One has giv'n, &dagger; Ev'n His Begotten Son <HI>[for it,]</HI> &dagger; <HI>This has He done,</HI> that who&s;oev'r &dagger; Believes aright in Him <HI>[alone,]</HI> &dagger; &s;hould never peri&s;h, but &s;hould have &dagger; an Everla&s;ting Life <HI>[by Him.]</HI> &dagger;</P>
</DIV3>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="18" TYPE="part">
<PB N="419" REF="001946_0456_0FFE5B094CDD1F10">
<HEAD>XVIII. The Ble&s;&s;ing.</HEAD>
<DIV3 TYPE="section">
<HEAD><HI>Act.</HI> III. 26.</HEAD>
<P>GOD Rai&s;ing His Son Jo&s;us, hath &dagger; &s;ent Him to Ble&s;s you <HI>all,</HI> &dagger; in turning ev'ry one of you &dagger; from his Iniquities. &dagger;</P>
</DIV3>
<DIV3 TYPE="section">
<HEAD><HI>Act.</HI> V. 31.</HEAD>
<P>Him God with His Right hand &s;ets up, &dagger; a Prince and Saviour &dagger; to give <HI>His</HI> I&s;rael to repent, &dagger; and to forgive <HI>their</HI> Sins. &dagger;</P>
</DIV3>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="19" TYPE="part">
<HEAD>XIX. The Holy Bapti&s;m.</HEAD>
<HEAD TYPE="sub"><HI>Matth.</HI> XXVIII. 19, 20.</HEAD>
<P>ALL Nations make Di&s;ciples, them &Verbar; Baptizing in the Name &Verbar; of <HI>GOD</HI> the Father and the Son&Verbar; and of the Holy Spirit. &Verbar; In&s;tructing them, that <HI>there|upon</HI> &Verbar; they carefully ob&s;erve &Verbar; all things whatever they may be &Verbar; I have commanded you. &Verbar;</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="20" TYPE="part">
<HEAD>XX. The Holy Supper.</HEAD>
<HEAD TYPE="sub">1 <HI>Cor.</HI> XI. 23&mdash;26.</HEAD>
<P><HI>KNow,</HI> The Lord Je&s;us in the Night &dagger; in which He was betray'd, &dagger; took Bread and having given Thanks, &dagger; He brake <HI>it and</HI> He &s;aid: &dagger; Take, Eat; This is my Body which &dagger; is Broken <HI>thus</HI> for you: &dagger; This do, that &s;o of me you may &dagger; keep the Remem|brance up. &dagger; He al&s;o in like manner <HI>took</HI> &dagger; the Cup, when He had Supp'd; &dagger; &s;aid, This is the New-Te&s;ta|ment, &dagger; <HI>confirmed</HI> in my Blood. &dagger; This is what I would have you do, &dagger; as often as you Drink &dagger; <HI>of this,</HI> that &s;o of me you may &dagger; keep the Remembrance up. &dagger; As oft now as ye Eat this Bread, &dagger; and as ye Drink this Cup, &dagger; you the Death of the Lord &s;how forth &dagger; until that He do come. &dagger;</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="21" TYPE="part">
<HEAD>XXI. Our Attonement.</HEAD>
<HEAD TYPE="sub"><HI>Roman,</HI> Chap. V.</HEAD>
<P N="6">6 WHen we were [<HI>who&s;ty</HI>] de&s;titute of &s;trength, &dagger; This [<HI>proper</HI>] time, CHRIST dy'd for the profane. &dagger;</P>
<P N="7"><PB N="420" REF="001946_0457_0FFE5B110A435D78">
7 'Tis <HI>[Very]</HI> true, One for a Ju&s;t Man would &dagger; <HI>[Scarce and]</HI> with no &s;mall difficulty dye. &dagger; Yet perad|venture &s;omr would <HI>[Even]</HI> dare &dagger; for a <HI>[Bels<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="2 letters">]</HI> Good Man to &s;uffer Death. &dagger;</P>
<P N="8">8 But God commends <HI>[in this]</HI> His Love to us &dagger; that CHRIST for us <HI>[altho']</HI> yet Sinners dy'd. &dagger;</P>
<P N="9">9 Much more then <HI>we [may well] <HI>infer from hence,</HI></HI> &dagger; &s;ince by His Blood we're <HI>[freely]</HI> ju&s;tify'd, &dagger; we &s;hall through Him be <HI>[&s;urely]</HI> &s;aved from &dagger; the wrath <HI>to which we <HI>[Ju&s;tly] <HI>are expos'd.</HI></HI></HI> &dagger;</P>
<P N="10">10 For if by His Sons Death <HI>[for it]</HI> we were &dagger; while yet Foes <HI>[fully]</HI> reconcil'd to God, &dagger; much more be &s;ure now <HI>[&s;o well]</HI> reconcil'd, &dagger; we &s;hall be &s;aved by His <HI>[Glozious]</HI> Life. &dagger;</P>
<P N="11">11 And yet this not all <HI>[of it]</HI> but we &dagger; do here|withal rejoyce in God <HI>[our God,]</HI> &dagger; Thro' our Lord Je&s;us Chri&s;t, by whom <HI>[it is]</HI> &dagger; <HI>[a full]</HI> Atonement we have now receiv'd. &dagger;</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="22" TYPE="part">
<HEAD>XXII. Spiritual Ble&s;&s;ings.</HEAD>
<HEAD TYPE="sub">Eph. <HI>I.</HI></HEAD>
<P N="3">3 O Ble&s;ted be the <HI>Glorious</HI> God &dagger; and Father of our Lord, &dagger; Even of our Lord Je&s;us Chri&s;t, &dagger; who hath now ble&s;&s;ed us; &dagger; with all the Ble&s;&s;ings which are of &dagger; a Spiritual import &dagger; in Heav'nly places; &dagger; in and with, &dagger; a CHRIST <HI>to be enjoy'd,</HI> &dagger;</P>
<P N="4">4 According as in Him He hath &dagger; made a free choice of us &dagger; before that the Foundation of &dagger; the World was ever laid. &dagger; <HI>Chu&s;ing us</HI> upon this intent &dagger; that we be|fore Him &s;hould &dagger; be holy and be blamele&s;s, thro' &dagger; the influence of love. &dagger;</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="23" TYPE="part">
<HEAD>XXIII. Great Things done for us in CHRIST.</HEAD>
<HEAD TYPE="sub">Eph. <HI>II.</HI></HEAD>
<P N="4">4 A God, who in the Riches of &dagger; His Mercy doth abound, &dagger; becau&s;e of the great love wherewith &dagger; He &s;till hath loved us. &dagger;</P>
<P N="6"><PB N="421" REF="001946_0458_0FFE5B12E588D360">
6 Even when we were dead in Sins, &dagger; He hath enliven'd us, &dagger; together with CHRIST <HI>doing it;</HI> &dagger; Saved you are by Grace! &dagger;</P>
<P N="6">6 Us al&s;o hath He rai&s;ed up &dagger; together, and He has &dagger; in Heav'nly Places made us fir &dagger; in Je&s;us Chri&s;t together &dagger;</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="24" TYPE="part">
<HEAD>XXIV. The Scale of Heaven.</HEAD>
<HEAD TYPE="sub"><HI>Rom.</HI> VIII.</HEAD>
<P N="30">30 WHom He did <HI>fir&s;t</HI> prede&s;tinate, &dagger; them he did al&s;o call; &dagger; and them whom he has called, He &dagger; hath al&s;o Ju&s;tify'd, &dagger; and whom He Ju&s;tify'd, He tho&s;e &dagger; has al&s;o glorify'd. &dagger;</P>
<P N="31">31 Unto &s;uch things as the&s;e then what &dagger; is there that we &s;hall &s;ay? &dagger; If God be once engag'd for us &dagger; again&s;t us who can be? &dagger;</P>
<P N="32">32 He who his own Son &s;pared not, &dagger; <HI>when Ju&s;tice made Demands,</HI> &dagger; but did deliver him to <HI>Death</HI> &dagger; in the room of us all, &dagger; How &s;han't He al&s;o freely give &dagger; all things to us with Him? &dagger;</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="25" TYPE="part">
<HEAD>XXV. Conjugal Goodne&s;s.</HEAD>
<HEAD TYPE="sub">Eph. <HI>V.</HI></HEAD>
<P N="21">21 WIves, Unto your own Husbands yeild, &dagger; even as to the Lord. &dagger;</P>
<P N="23">23 The Husband is head to the Wife, &dagger; as CHRIST Head to the Church. &dagger;</P>
<P N="24">24 For this Cau&s;e, as the Church is in &dagger; &s;ubjection un|to CHRIST, &dagger; Wives unto their own Husbands &s;hould &dagger; in every thing be &s;o. &dagger;</P>
<P N="25">25 Husbands O do you love your Wives &dagger; <HI>with all due tenderne&s;s,</HI> &dagger; as CHRIST has al&s;o lov'd the Church, &dagger; and gave him&s;elf for it. &dagger;</P>
<P N="28">28 As Men love their own Bodies, &s;o &dagger; they ought to Love their Wives; &dagger; He who does duly love his Wife, &dagger; does therein love him&s;elf. &dagger;</P>
<P N="33">33 Let each and every one of you &dagger; love his Wife as him&s;elf: &dagger; and let the Wife &s;ee that &s;he pay &dagger; her Hus|band much Regard. &dagger;</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="26" TYPE="part">
<PB N="422" REF="001946_0459_0FFE5F05621EC590">
<HEAD>XXVI. The Song of the Twenty-Four Elders.</HEAD>
<HEAD TYPE="sub"><HI>Rev.</HI> IV.</HEAD>
<P>WOrthy Thou art, O Lord; &dagger; for to receive <HI>from all</HI> &dagger; Glory and Honour too &dagger; and power; for that thou did&s;t &dagger; all things create; &dagger; and for thy will they are and were &dagger; created <HI>all.</HI> &dagger;</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="27" TYPE="part">
<HEAD>XXVII. Prai&s;es for the Men of Judah.</HEAD>
<HEAD TYPE="sub"><HI>Jude.</HI> 24, 25.</HEAD>
<P>NOW unto Him who has &dagger; the power to pre&s;erve &dagger; you free from Sinful falls, &dagger; and to &s;et you before &dagger; the face of His &dagger; bright Glory, free from fault, with a &dagger; Triumphant Joy; &dagger; To Him who's only wi&s;e &dagger; God, <HI>Ev'n</HI> our Saviour, &dagger; Glory and Grandeur be, &dagger; Power and Dominion; &dagger; Now at this time &dagger; let it be &s;o and &s;o unto &dagger; all Ages be. &dagger;</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="28" TYPE="part">
<HEAD>XXVIII. The New Song.</HEAD>
<DIV3 TYPE="section">
<HEAD><HI>Rev.</HI> V. 9, 10.</HEAD>
<P>O <HI>Lamb of God,</HI> Thou art &dagger; worthy to take the Book, &dagger; and open all the Seals &dagger; which cover what's in it; &dagger; For thou wa&s;t Slain, &dagger; and ha&s;t redeem'd us unto God &dagger; by thine own Blood. &dagger; So from each Kindred, and &dagger; Language and People and &dagger; Nation <HI>thou bringe&s;t us;</HI> &dagger; and thou ha&s;t made us to be &dagger; both Kings and Prie&s;ts &dagger; unto our God, and we &s;hall Reign &dagger; over the Earth. &dagger;</P>
<P>[With the voice of the many Angels.]</P>
</DIV3>
<DIV3 TYPE="section">
<HEAD><HI>Rev.</HI> V. 12.</HEAD>
<P>Oh! worthy is the Lamb, &dagger; <HI>the Lamb,</HI> that has been Slain, &dagger; <HI>all</HI> Power and Riches and &dagger; Wi&s;dom and Forti|tude &dagger; and Honour too &dagger; with Glory and with Ble&s;&s;ing &s;till &dagger; for to receive. &dagger;</P>
</DIV3>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="29" TYPE="part">
<HEAD>XXIX. The Doxology.</HEAD>
<HEAD TYPE="sub"><HI>Rev.</HI> 1.5, 6.</HEAD>
<P>NOW to that <HI>Glorious One</HI> who has &dagger; wondrou&s;ly loved <HI>[&s;inful]</HI> us, &dagger; and who has made us to be Kings &dagger; as well as <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="3 letters">e&s;ts to God <HI>[on High;]</HI> &dagger; <HI>Even unto the God,</HI> whom &dagger; His Father; <HI>[let there]</HI> unto Him &dagger; be Glory and <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="4 letters">nion &dagger; forever more. Amen: <HI>[amen<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">]</HI> &dagger;</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="30" TYPE="part">
<PB N="423" REF="001946_0460_0FFE51D2B39AD0C0">
<HEAD>XXX. The Name of God.</HEAD>
<DIV3 TYPE="section">
<HEAD><HI>Prov.</HI> XVIII. 10.</HEAD>
<P>JEHOVAH's <HI>[Great and]</HI> Glorious Name, &dagger; it is a Tower of Strength: &dagger; The Righteous runs <HI>[with &s;peed]</HI> into't; &dagger; and there on high Sits &s;afe. &dagger;</P>
</DIV3>
<DIV3 TYPE="section">
<HEAD><HI>Exod.</HI> XXXIV. 6, 7.</HEAD>
<P>So He proclaimed it <HI>[of Did]</HI> &dagger; JEHOVAH is <HI>His Name;</HI> &dagger; JEHOVAH who is <HI>[the Strong]</HI> God &dagger; <HI>for|ever</HI> merciful &dagger; and <HI>[berv]</HI> Gracious too is He; &dagger; to anger very Slow; &dagger; yea, He does <HI>[very]</HI> much abound &dagger; in Grace and Truth <HI>to us.</HI> &dagger; He does <HI>[how Great]</HI> re|&s;erves of Grace &dagger; for many Thou&s;ands keep! &dagger; Iniquity He <HI>[freely]</HI> does &dagger; di&s;pence a pardon to. &dagger; Yea, to Tran&s;|gre&s;&s;ion too <HI>[tis done]</HI> &dagger; and to <HI>all &s;orts</HI> of Sin; &dagger; and if He do <HI>[in part]</HI> cut off &dagger; He will not quite cut off. &dagger;</P>
</DIV3>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="31" TYPE="part">
<HEAD>XXXI. Right Sabbatizing.</HEAD>
<DIV3 TYPE="section">
<HEAD>THE FIRST PART. <HI>I&s;ai.</HI> LVI. 1, 2, 6, 7.</HEAD>
<P>THus the ETERNAL God hath &s;aid, &dagger; Ble&s;&s;ings attend the <HI>[Pious]</HI> Man &dagger; who does this, and the Son of Man &dagger; who lays <HI>[and keeps]</HI> fa&s;t hold on it; &dagger; <HI>The Man</HI> who from polluting it &dagger; does keep the <HI>[Holy]</HI> Sabbath well; &dagger; and he who from the doing of &dagger; all Evil keeps his hand <HI>[with care.]</HI> &dagger;</P>
<P>Yea, The Sons of the Stranger, who &dagger; to <HI>[and on]</HI> the ETERNAL God &dagger; do join them&s;elves, that they may be &dagger; true <HI>[Prie&s;ts and]</HI> Servants unto tree: &dagger; And that in Love unto the Name &dagger; of <HI>[Him who's]</HI> the ETERNAL GOD, &dagger; they may become the Servants, who &dagger; <HI>[truly]</HI> devote them&s;elves to Him; &dagger; all of the&s;e will my Sabbath keep &dagger; from all pollutions <HI>[clean and]</HI> elear, &dagger; and they upon my Covenant &dagger; will take <HI>[therein]</HI> perpetual hold. &dagger;</P>
<P>Now &s;uch as the&s;e I will into &dagger; my Holy Mountain <HI>[&s;urely]</HI> bring; &dagger; and in my Hou&s;e of Pray'r I will &dagger;
<PB N="424" REF="001946_0461_0FFE5F06E923EFC8">make them to &s;hine with <HI>[Glorious]</HI> Joy. &dagger; Their Off'rings which a&s;cend in Flames, &dagger; and <HI>[all the]</HI> Sacrifi|ces which &dagger; they Offer on my Altar, &s;hall &dagger; a good <HI>[and kind]</HI> Acceptance find. &dagger; For that my Hou&s;e, <HI>to which they do &dagger; for &s;uch Devotions [u&s;e to] go,</HI> &dagger; it &s;hall be call'd, an Hou&s;e of Pray'r, &dagger; free for all People <HI>[coming]</HI> there. &dagger;</P>
</DIV3>
<DIV3 TYPE="section">
<HEAD>THE SECOND PART. <HI>I&s;ai.</HI> LVIII. 13, 14.</HEAD>
<P>IF thou from the profaning of &dagger; the Sabbath turn <HI>[away]</HI> thy Foot: not doing of thy plea&s;ure on &dagger; what is <HI>[ordain'd]</HI> my Holy day; &dagger; But if the Sabbath thou e&s;teem &dagger; <HI>[and keep]</HI> as a Delight unto &dagger; the <HI>Ble&s;s'd</HI> JEHOVAH's Holy one, &dagger; ev'n <HI>[Him who's]</HI> the Victo|rious One; &dagger; And if thereon thou honour Him, &dagger; not doing as thou'rt us'd <HI>[to do,]</HI> &dagger; nor plea&s;ing thy own hu|mour now, &dagger; nor Speaking a wrong word <HI>[thereon.]</HI> &dagger;</P>
<P>Then thou &s;halt &s;atisfy thy &s;elf &dagger; <HI>[Ever]</HI> in the ETER|NAL God; &dagger; And I will make thee Ride upon &dagger; High <HI>[and Rich]</HI> places of the Earth. &dagger; I will thee with the portion of &dagger; Jacob thy Father <HI>[always]</HI> feed; &dagger; For &s;o now &s;peaks the very mouth &dagger; of the <HI>[True and]</HI> ETER|NAL God. &dagger;</P>
</DIV3>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="32" TYPE="part">
<HEAD>XXXII. Early Piety.</HEAD>
<HEAD TYPE="sub"><HI>Eccle.</HI> XI. 9, 10. XII. 1, 14.</HEAD>
<P>REjoyce, O Young Man, in thy Youth, &dagger; and be of a good Heart &dagger; in the Days of thy Youth, <HI>to this</HI> &dagger; <HI>thou art enough inclin'd!</HI> &dagger; And walk thou in the ways pre&s;er'd &dagger; by &s;uch an Heart as thine; &dagger; Do what &s;hall &s;eem de&s;ireable &dagger; unto thy <HI>Youthful</HI> Eyes. &dagger; But know thou that for all of the&s;e &dagger; <HI>indulg'd Enormatimes,</HI> &dagger; God the judge will bring thee <HI>anon</HI>&dagger;to render an Account&dagger;</P>
<P>Oh, then remove thou from thine heart, &dagger; <HI>what cau&s;|es</HI> Grief and Wrath; &dagger; and from thy Fle&s;h, Oh, do thou cau&s;e &dagger; each Vitious lu&s;t to pa&s;s, &dagger; For Infancy, and then the Youth &dagger; which is the Morning time, &dagger; is Va|nity: <HI>I&s; &s;pent in Sin,</HI> &dagger; <HI>it is all &s;pant in vain.</HI> &dagger;</P>
<P><PB N="425" REF="001946_0462_0FFE5F08A4CBDC60">
Remember thy Creator now &dagger; <HI>(the Father, Sen, and Spirit;) Now</HI> in the Days of thy Youth, * which &dagger; are of thy choice the Days. &dagger; <HI>Do it,</HI> before the Evil Days &dagger; do come, and years draw nigh &dagger; in which thou &s;halt <HI>have cau&s;e</HI> to &s;ay, &dagger; I've no Delight in them. &dagger;</P>
<P>For GOD the Judge will every Work &dagger; into a Judgment bring; &dagger; with every Secret; be't a good &dagger; or be't an evil thing. &dagger;</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="33" TYPE="part">
<HEAD>XXXIII. Alms-Giving.</HEAD>
<DIV3 TYPE="section">
<HEAD><HI>Luk.</HI> XII. 33, 34.</HEAD>
<P>SEll your Po&s;&s;e&s;&s;ions, <HI>rather than</HI> &Verbar; <HI>leave &s;uch a thing undone:</HI> &Verbar; And freely giving <HI>what you have,</HI> &Verbar; Mer|ciful Alms di&s;pen&s;e. &Verbar; <HI>By doing &s;o</HI> provide yourlelves &Verbar; of Bags that won't decay; &Verbar; a Trea&s;ure in the Heavens, which &Verbar; is certain not to fail: &Verbar; Where 'tis no Thief can make approach, &Verbar; nor can a Moth corrupt. &Verbar; For where your Trea&s;ure is laid up, &Verbar; your Heart will &s;till be there. &Verbar;</P>
</DIV3>
<DIV3 TYPE="section">
<HEAD><HI>Heb.</HI> XIII. 16.</HEAD>
<P>Be &s;ure that you by no means be &Verbar; forgetful of <HI>this thing;</HI> &Verbar; To be Beneficent, and be &Verbar; Communicative &s;till: &Verbar; For with &s;uch Sacrifices as &Verbar; are in &s;uch things as the&s;e, &Verbar; the GOD, <HI>who does behold them all,</HI> &Verbar; is highly gratify'd. &Verbar;</P>
</DIV3>
<DIV3 TYPE="section">
<HEAD><HI>Act.</HI> X. 4.</HEAD>
<P>The Supplications thou haft made &Verbar; <HI>unto the Glorious GOD,</HI> &Verbar; and there withal thy Gracious Alms &Verbar; that have attended them; &Verbar; The&s;e <HI>Off'rings</HI> have made their A&s;|cent; &Verbar; for a Memorial, &Verbar; in the &s;ight of the <HI>Ble&s;&s;ed</HI> GOD, &Verbar; <HI>who &s;till remembers them.</HI> &Verbar;</P>
</DIV3>
<DIV3 TYPE="section">
<HEAD><HI>Eccl.</HI> XI. 1.</HEAD>
<P>Ca&s;t thou thy Corn-for-&s;eed upon &Verbar; the face of moi&s;tned Ground: &Verbar; For after many days thou &s;halt &Verbar; find <HI>the return of</HI> it. &Verbar;</P>
</DIV3>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="34" TYPE="part">
<HEAD>XXXIV. The Ten Commandments.</HEAD>
<DIV3 TYPE="section">
<P N="1">I BEfore my face, thou &s;halt not have &Verbar; Other, and After Gods, <HI>for thine</HI> &Verbar;</P>
<P N="2"><PB N="426" REF="001946_0463_0FFE5F0EA6418C70">
II. Thou &s;halt not any Image make &Verbar; to thee, nor bow thy &s;elf thereto. &Verbar;</P>
<P N="3">III. Thou &s;halt not take in vain the Name &Verbar; of the ETERNAL One, Thy GOD. &Verbar;</P>
<P N="4">IV. Remember thou the Sabbath-Day, &Verbar; that thou may&s;t it as Holy keep. &Verbar;</P>
<P N="5">V. Thy Father and thy Mother pay, &Verbar; Honour, that &s;o they may prolong&Verbar; thy Days upon the <HI>promis'd</HI> Earth. &Verbar;</P>
<P N="6">VI. Kill not <HI>in any Murd'rous way.</HI> &Verbar;</P>
<P N="7">VII. Commit thou no Adultery. &Verbar;</P>
<P N="8">VIII. Thou &s;halt not any Stealth Commit. &Verbar;</P>
<P N="9">IX. Upon thy Neighbour bear thou not &Verbar; a Te&s;ti|mony that is fal&s;e. &Verbar;</P>
<P N="10">X. Thou &s;halt not Covet any thing &Verbar; which to thy Neighbour does belong. &Verbar;</P>
</DIV3>
<DIV3 TYPE="section">
<HEAD>1 <HI>John</HI> V. 3.</HEAD>
<P>This is the Love of GOD; and His &Verbar; Command|ments never grievous are. &Verbar;</P>
</DIV3>
</DIV2>
<TRAILER>FINIS.</TRAILER>
</DIV1>
